---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = new Date('2026-07-23');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Ayomiposi Sotomi"
  description="How this site handles your data — in short, it barely does."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl font-medium text-text md:text-5xl">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-text-secondary">
      Last updated:{' '}
      {lastUpdated.toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
        month: 'long',
        day: 'numeric',
        year: 'numeric',
        timeZone: 'UTC',
      })}
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-neutral mt-10 max-w-none">
      <p>
        This site is static — Markdown files rendered into HTML, with no
        server, no database, and no user accounts. That keeps what it can
        collect about you to almost nothing by construction, not just by
        policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This site does not use cookies. No tracking cookies, no
        analytics cookies, no "essential" cookies used as a workaround. If
        that ever changes, this page will be updated first.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        This site uses <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a>,
        which is cookieless and does not track individuals across sites or
        build a profile of you. It reports aggregate, anonymized metrics
        like page views and country-level location — nothing that
        identifies you personally.
      </p>

      <h2>Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        This site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. Cloudflare may process
        standard connection metadata (like your IP address) as part of
        serving the site, the same way any web host does.
      </p>

      <h2>Comments and newsletter</h2>
      <p>
        Comments and a newsletter signup are planned but not live yet. When
        they launch, this policy will be updated to describe exactly what
        those services (Cusdis for comments, Buttondown for the newsletter)
        collect and how — before they go live, not after.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Since no personal data is collected through this site right now,
        there's nothing to request access to, correct, or delete. If that
        changes, this section will explain how to exercise those rights
        under GDPR and similar regulations.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        <!-- DRAFT: add your preferred contact method here before publishing. -->
        Reach out via GitHub if you have questions about this policy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
